a.xlink:title: The full, self-contained description of a printed circuit board. This is the root of a board .lht file. The * after the v in the name is an integer which is the format version.
Any meta-data that won't directly turn into physical material (e.g. copper).
physical layer stack information: geometry and properties of physical layers
font kit: all fonts used on the board (if no font specified, default font will be used)
routing styles hash: collection of all available routing syles
